## 1. Zero Tolerance for Inline Styles & CSS Hacks
- **Mobile-First:** Write default CSS for mobile, use `@media (min-width)` for desktop.
- **SCSS Modules Only:** ALWAYS use `.module.scss`. NEVER use `style={{...}}`.
- **Clean CSS:** NO magic numbers (use variables). NO "fix" files.
- **No !important:** Use specificity to manage styles. **Exception:** You may use `!important` ONLY when strictly necessary to override stubborn third-party/vendor styles that cannot be controlled via specificity.

## 2. Internationalization (i18n) First
- NEVER use hardcoded strings.
- ALWAYS use `next-intl` (e.g., `t('key')`).

## 3. Modern Next.js Architecture
- **Server Components Default:** Add `'use client'` ONLY when interactivity is needed.
- **Images & Links:** Use `next/image` and `next/link` ONLY.
- **Fonts:** Use `next/font` variables.

## 4. UI Kit & Reusability (Don't Reinvent)
- **Check First:** Look in `@/components/common/` before building.
- **Mandatory Usage:**
    - Use `Button` (not `<a>` or `<button>`).
    - Use `FormInput` & `FormTextArea` (not `<input>`).

## 5. Strict TypeScript & Props
- **No `any`:** Strict zero tolerance.
- **Interfaces:** Define `interface Props` for every component.

## 6. Accessibility (a11y) & Semantics
- **Tags:** Use semantic HTML (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`).
- **Labels:** Interactive elements must have `aria-label`.

## 7. Responsive Responsibility
- **Laptop Safe:** Navigation MUST be visible on Laptops (1200px+).
- **Mobile Safe:** No overflow on small screens.

## 8. Development Hygiene
- **Imports:** Use absolute paths (`@/components/...`).
- **Cleanup:** Remove unused imports/logs immediately.
- **Verify:** ALWAYS run `npm run build` before confirming. 
